  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed using Monte Carlo propagation of inlet flow-rate and rotational-speed tolerances across the five operating points; a screening sensitivity study comparing first-order Sobol indices was conducted internally and summarized in the UQ report narrative. Dominant contributors were identified verbally as rotational speed and impeller tip clearance; however, no structured sensitivity-analysis record has been linked to this package.",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
