      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version control with documented test suite; all simulation scripts archived in institutional repository.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 was used under a validated installation qualified per ISO 9001 procedures. Version control records and regression test logs confirm Gradation 2 compliance. No code modifications were applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through benchmark test cases relevant to internal rotating flow.",
      "rationale": "The solver was verified against the ASME V&V 20 lid-driven cavity and Taylor-Couette benchmarks. Residual norms converged to 1e-6 for all governing equations across all operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for relative hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% at the nominal operating point.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M elements) was conducted at the 3500 RPM / 5 L/min operating point. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI of 3.1% for the NIH hemolysis index, satisfying the acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with traceability to calibrated instrumentation; inlet flow rate and rotational speed must be controlled within ±2% of nominal.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump experimental data (Hariharan et al.) documents controlled flow conditions with calibrated Coriolis flowmeters (±0.5%) and encoder-verified speed (±10 RPM). Temperature was maintained at 37 ± 0.5 °C matching blood-analogue viscosity targets."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized index of agreement for hemolysis index across 5 operating points must exceed 0.85; individual point error must not exceed 20%.",
      "rationale": "NIH hemolysis index predictions agreed with experimental measurements with a mean absolute error of 11.4% and normalized index of agreement of 0.91 across all five operating points. Worst-case single-point error was 17.8% at the 2500 RPM / 3 L/min condition, within the acceptance bound."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation (NIH hemolysis index) must be directly mappable to the COU decision metric (relative hemolysis index RH).",
      "rationale": "NIH hemolysis index is the direct experimental observable from which RH is derived via normalization against predicate device measurements. The mapping is analytic and lossless; no surrogate QoI substitution was required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must cover the same pump geometry and at least 3 of the 5 COU operating points.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at all five COU operating points. Blood-analogue fluid properties matched COU haematocrit targets. The validation scenario is assessed as substantially representative of the COU physical regime."
    },
    {
