      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection is addressed through validation evidence.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published literature for rotating blood pump flows. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2; adequacy is supported by the output comparison evidence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties must be traceable to measurement or published reference data; input uncertainty ranges must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles were derived from ultrasonic Doppler measurements. Blood-analogue viscosity was characterized by cone-plate rheometry (±3%). Rotational speed was set from encoder telemetry. Input uncertainty ranges for flow rate (±2%), speed (±10 RPM), and fluid viscosity (±3%) were documented in the UQ report. A screening sensitivity study using first-order Sobol indices was performed and summarized narratively in that report, identifying rotational speed and impeller tip clearance as the dominant contributors to hemolysis index variance; these findings informed the Monte Carlo propagation bounds used in the UQ analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
